Sir Nicholas Maxted Fenn  (19 February 1936 – 18 September 2016) was a British diplomat. He was High Commissioner to India from 1991 to 1996.
Fenn served as a RAF pilot in the 1950s before his diplomatic and civil service career. Fenn later studied at Cambridge University.He lived in Marden, Kent.
